Subscription and Plan Management API
====================================

This gateway now exposes subscription and plan management routes alongside auth.

Available routes
----------------

- GET `/subscriptionservice/plans` - view active plans
- GET `/subscriptionservice/plans/{plan_id}` - inspect one plan
- POST `/subscriptionservice/plans/search` - intelligent search by need or keyword
- GET `/subscriptionservice/plans/search?query=...` - same search via query parameter
- POST `/subscriptionservice/subscriptions` - subscribe a user to a plan
- GET `/subscriptionservice/subscriptions/{subscription_id}` - track a subscription
- GET `/subscriptionservice/subscriptions/user/{user_id}` - list a user's subscriptions
- PATCH `/subscriptionservice/subscriptions/{subscription_id}/status` - update status
- POST `/subscriptionservice/subscriptions/{subscription_id}/change` - change plans

Sample SQL tables
-----------------

```sql
CREATE TABLE users (
	user_id VARCHAR(64) PRIMARY KEY,
	fullname VARCHAR(120) NOT NULL,
	phone VARCHAR(30),
	email VARCHAR(120) UNIQUE NOT NULL,
	password VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
	created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE plans (
	plan_id VARCHAR(64) PRIMARY KEY,
	name VARCHAR(120) NOT NULL,
	description TEXT NOT NULL,
	price DECIMAL(10,2) NOT NULL,
	billing_cycle VARCHAR(20) NOT NULL,
	active BOOLEAN DEFAULT TRUE,
	created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE subscriptions (
	subscription_id VARCHAR(64) PRIMARY KEY,
	user_id VARCHAR(64) NOT NULL,
	plan_id VARCHAR(64) NOT NULL,
	status VARCHAR(20) NOT NULL,
	started_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
	updated_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
	next_billing_date TIMESTAMP,
	FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id),
	FOREIGN KEY (plan_id) REFERENCES plans(plan_id)
);
```

Setup
-----

1. Activate the virtual environment with `venv\Scripts\activate`.
2. Install dependencies with `pip install -r requirements.txt`.
3. Run the gateway with `python run.py`.